This paper deals with the computation of the minimum distance of a linear code, which is a key concept in information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also focuses on distributed-memory architectures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves experimental results, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
